query: I encountered a phishing scam via SMS. It was from a number, and they claimed I had outstanding bills with DBS. The phone number was +6591322047. Yes, I clicked on the link in the message to verify my identity it seemed legitimate. The link directed me to a site that looked just like DBS's official website. I thought it was real, so I entered my card credentials there. The website was quite convincing; it had the right logo and layout, so I didn't notice any misspellings or anything that raised a red flag at the time. It looked very similar to the real DBS website, which made it harder to recognize as a scam. I just want to add that after I entered my details, I noticed unauthorized transactions had occurred. A total of $225.90 was transferred to a Citibank account on April 7. That's when I realized something was wrong.
